1.title: Full
1.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a kitchen and fill up lots of items with water. At home, they have watermelon fruit tea until they are full.

2.title: Underneath
2.plot: The Twirlwoos visit a hat shop. Chickadee and Chick are underneath a hat that gets bought, so Great Big Hoo and Toodle-oo follow whilst underneath their own hats. At home, the Twirlywoos are visited by the box. The box contains a rainbow, and the Twirlwoos end up underneath it.

3.title: Round & Round
3.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a playground, and go round and round on a roundabout. At home, the Twirlywoos are visited by the Stop Go Car, who goes round and round the boat.

4.title: Up
4.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a back garden, where they watch a man hanging laundry up on a line. Chickedy and Chick get into the laundry basket, and the man accidentally hangs them up on the line too!

5.title: Connecting
5.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a bus stop and learn about connecting with shoelaces. At home, the Very Important Lady visits.

6.title: Noisy
6.plot: The Twirlywoos visit the house of a woman who is trying to nap, and learn about noisy music with a radio. At home, the Twirlywoos are visited by the Stop Go Car.

7.title: All Gone
7.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a kitchen, where they learn about 'all gone' - and make some cakes all gone. At home, the Twirlwoos have fruit tea, but the tea keeps being 'all gone'.

8.title: Behind
8.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a park and play with a baby. At home, the Twirlywoos watch a cartoon on the Twirlywoo Screen.

9.title: This Way That Way
9.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a park, where they watch a lady throwing a ball for a dog. The ball lands where they are hiding, and they start to mimic the lady and the dog, with Toodloo throwing the ball for Chickedy and Chick to fetch.

10.title: Up & Down
10.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a back garden, where they watch a boy bouncing a ball up and down. The ball bounces out of his hands and lands in the bush where the Twirlywoos are hiding.

11.title: Over
11.plot:

12.title: Shorter & Shorter
12.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a bedroom, where they watch a man sleeping under a knitted blanket. The Twirlywoos see a loose bit of wool from the end of the blanket get caught on the bed, and it starts to unravel.

13.title: Wrapping
13.plot:

14.title: Gone
14.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a toy train set, going through a tunnel. Back at home, the Twirlywoos try to have fruit tea, but it keeps disappearing.

15.title: Covering
15.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a garden, and they cover a lot of different things with a table cloth. Back at home, spots are flying around and covering everyone.

16.title: Coming and Going
16.plot: The Twirlywoos visit a bathroom, where a man is coming and going while running a bath. Back at home, the Stop Go Car keeps visiting and delivering balloons.

17.title: Through
17.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

18.title: Soft
18.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a bedroom, where a soft and fluffy cat is asleep on a bed. Chickedy and Chick can't resist petting the cat's soft fur, but they have to hide when a lady comes in and shoos the cat out of the room.

19.title: Pop
19.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a back garden, where a children's birthday party is going on. There is a machine that makes bubbles, and the Twirlywoos watch as the children have fun running around and popping them all.

20.title: Upside Down
20.plot: The Twirlywoos are at an art gallery, where they see a man hang a painting on the wall. He realizes he hung it upside down and turns it around. The Twirlywoos decide to turn all the paintings and sculptures in the room around!

1.title: Getting Wet
1.plot: The Twirlywoos are in a garden, where they watch a gardener watering plants. As she comes closer to them, they hide in a flowerbed. The hose runs through the flowerbed, and they all sit on it, stopping the flow of water!

2.title: Out
2.plot: Twirlywoo's learn about the concept of out in a painters workshop.

4.title: Inside
4.plot:

5.title: Going Over
5.plot: The Twirlywoos are at an equestrian center, where they hide behind a fence and see a horse and rider practicing going over a jump. They are interested in the idea of going over, so they decide to jump over the fence.

6.title: Rolling
6.plot: Rolling: The Twirlywoos are on top of a hill, where they watch a family with a picnic. The children are rolling down the hill. While they are away, the Twirlywoos decide to take things from the picnic and roll them down the hill too.

7.title: In and Out
7.plot: In and Out: The Twirlywoos are at a stable, where they watch as a man comes and leads a horse into the stable. When the man leaves, the Twirlywoos come out to investigate.

8.title: Cleaning
8.plot: Cleaning: The Twirlywoos are outside a café, where they watch a man cleaning the window. Another man sits down at the table with his coffee, only for the window cleaner to drip soapy water into his cup!

9.title: Louder and Louder
9.plot: Louder and Louder: The Twirlywoos watch a musician playing the drumst. He starts out playing softly, then gets louder until the Twirlywoos have to cover their ears. When he leaves, the Twirlywoos come out and start to investigate the drums.

10.title: Turning
10.plot: Turning: The Twirlywoos are in a back garden, where they watch a boy riding his bike. When his mom calls him inside, Chickedy and Chick run out and jump on the pedals of the bike, causing the bike to start moving.

11.title: Collecting
11.plot: Collecting: The Twirlywoos see some children collecting eggs, and decide to do some collecting of their own. Back in the boat, Peekaboo leaves them more things to collect.

12.title: Longer
12.plot: Longer: The Twirlywoos watch a baker rolling out a baguette, and get carried away when they try it for themselves. In the Boat, the Tea Machine is behaving oddly - the spout keeps on growing longer!

13.title: Bigger and Bigger
13.plot: Bigger: The Twirlywoos see children building a sandcastle at the beach, and decide to make it bigger. Back in the boat, they encounter a strange jelly which grows every time they touch it!

14.title: High and Low
14.plot: High and Low: The Twirlywoos learn about High and Low when they watch a lady trying to hang a mirror at the right height. Back in the Boat, the Twirlywoo Screen gives them a seesaw to play with.

15.title: Outside
15.plot: Outside: The Twirlywoos see a man take his chair out into the garden and decide to bring some more things outside. Meanwhile, Peekaboo gets stuck outside the Boat! Is Peekaboo able to get back in without being discovered?

16.title: Next To
16.plot: Next To: The Twirlywoos see a lady putting colored stars next to items in a shop window display, and they get carried away putting stars next to everything in sight!

17.title: Open and Close
17.plot: Open and Close: The Twirlywoos open and close the curtains on a stage, while a very important singer is trying to perform! There is more opening and closing when the Box comes to visit the Boat.

18.title: On Top Of
18.plot: On Top Of: In a clothes shop, the Twirlywoos get carried away putting one hat on top of another. Back in the Boat, Peekaboo is surprised to be on top of the tea machine.

19.title: Balancing
19.plot: Balancing: The Twirlywoos find out balancing is harder than it looks, when they copy a gymnast on a balance beam. Back in the Boat, Peekaboo's spring cleaning leaves a wobbly obstacle course for the Twirlywoos to balance on.

20.title: Joining Up
20.plot: Joining Up: The Twirlywoos see a hiker joining things onto his rucksack, and they decide to add a few of their own. In the Boat, the Twirlywoo Screen provides some dots for the Twirlywoos to join up.

21.title: Fitting Together
21.plot: Fitting Together: The Twirlywoos learn how to fit pipes together when they create a surprising water feature. The Very Important Lady falls apart and needs some help fitting back together.

22.title: Spinning
22.plot: Spinning: The Twirlywoos watch a pot being made on a spinning wheel and decide to have a go themselves. Back in the Boat, the tea table is in a spin.

23.title: More and More
23.plot: More and More: The Twirlywoos learn about more and more when they watch a shopkeeper build up a display of apples. Back in the Boat, the Twirlywoo Screen creates a tree which gives more and more bananas every time the Twirlywoos touch it.

24.title: Taller and Taller
24.plot: Taller and Taller: The Twirlywoos watch a baker making a tower of profiteroles. They try to make a tower of their own and get carried away!

25.title: Smaller
25.plot: Smaller: The Twirlywoos learn about small things when they pursue a tiny butterfly around a butterfly house. Back in the Boat, they are tickled by a mysterious creature who keeps on getting smaller to avoid being caught.

26.title: Twirling
26.plot: Twirling: The Twirlywoos learn about spinning around when they visit an ice rink and try to copy a skater's moves. The Box brings them a grass skirt which makes its wearer spin around!

27.title: Faster and Faster
27.plot: Faster and Faster: The Twirlywoos play a tune on a piano which gets faster and faster, while two dancers try to keep up! Back in the Boat, the Twirlywoo Screen sets them a speedy challenge.

28.title: On and Off
28.plot: On and Off: A sunbather tries to keep his hat on, while the Twirlywoos keep taking it off! Back in the Boat, the Very Important Lady is having trouble keeping herself together.

29.title: Hiding
29.plot: Hiding: A treasure hunt at a children's birthday party turns into a game of hide and seek, as the Twirlywoos try to avoid being found. Back in the Boat, the Twirlywoos are hidden by strange weeds which grow out of the floor!

30.title: Pulling
30.plot: Pulling: The Twirlywoos have a tug of war with a carpenter when they pull on the end of her tape measure. Back in the Boat, the Twirlywoos find a vine coming out of Peekaboo's house and can't resist giving it a pull.

imdb.plot outline: The four Twirlywoos - Great Big Hoo, Toodle-oo, Chickadee and Chick - have adventures both in the real world, and in their boat. They learn about a new concept each episode. Shy Peekaboo also lives on the boat, and joins in without the Twirlywoos knowing. The boat sometimes gets visitors, including the Stop Go Car and the Very Important Lady.
